---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/base.astro";
import Row from "../components/Row.astro";
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";

const blogs = (await getCollection("blog")).splice(0, 3);
---

<style>
  .site-header {
    background: rgb(182, 211, 183);
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(250, 249, 222);
    text-align: center;
    display: flex;
    padding-top: 200px;
    padding-bottom: 100px;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgb(250, 249, 222);
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 2rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  h1:before {
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    bottom: 100%;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
    content: "";
    display: block;
    height: 100px;
    width: 100px;
    background: linear-gradient(var(--calm-blue), rgb(34, 84, 132));
    border-radius: 100px;
  }

  .intro {
    color: rgb(250, 249, 222);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>

<BaseLayout title="Welcome to Home School Coding Club">
  <header slot="header" class="site-header">
    <h1><a href="/">Home School Coding Club</a></h1>
    <p class="intro">Crafting Futures with Code</p>
  </header>
  <main>
    <section>
      <Row>
        <h2>The Language of Tomorrow's Innovators</h2>
        <p>
          Coding is the backbone of our increasingly digital existence, powering
          everything from the apps we use daily to the way we communicate and
          access information. Learning to code fosters problem-solving skills,
          logical thinking, and creativity, equipping individuals with the
          ability to not only understand but also shape the technology-driven
          future. It's a language of global dialogue, breaking down barriers and
          opening doors to countless opportunities across various industries. As
          technology continues to permeate every aspect of life, coding stands
          not just as a skill for employment, but as an essential tool for
          navigating, understanding, and contributing to the world of tomorrow.
        </p>
        <p>
          Additionally, coding fosters perseverance and resilience, as kids
          learn to troubleshoot and correct their errors. In an increasingly
          tech-driven world, coding literacy is as essential as traditional
          literacy. It opens doors to numerous career opportunities in various
          sectors, ensuring that children are equipped with the skills to
          succeed in a rapidly evolving job market. Moreover, early exposure to
          coding encourages inclusivity in the tech industry, breaking down
          barriers and stereotypes from a young age.
        </p>
      </Row>
      <Row>
        <h2>Unleashing Imagination, One Line of Code at a Time</h2>
        <p>
          Coding is not just about technology. It is not just about
          understanding computers. Coding is about nurturing problem-solving
          skills, logical thinking, and creativity. When children learn to code,
          they are also learning to break down complex problems into smaller,
          manageable parts. This analytical thinking is beneficial in various
          aspects of life and future professions.
        </p>
      </Row>
    </section>
    <section>
      <Row>
        <h2>Blog</h2>
        {
          blogs.map((blog) => {
            const url = `/blog/${blog.slug}`;
            return (
              <article>
                <h3>
                  <a href={url}>{blog.data.title}</a>
                </h3>
                <p>{blog.data.description}</p>
                <a href={url}>Read More</a>
              </article>
            );
          })
        }
      </Row>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
